<HEADLINE> Military Attaches in India Visit Jammu Borders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Military attaches of 25 foreign
missions in India Friday visited border areas of Rajouri and
Poonch in Jammu and Kashmir, the Press Trust of India (PTI)
reported.
</P>
<P>
Before the visit, the military attaches from New Delhi were
briefed by Indian Army authorities at Hagrota, 12 km from Jammu,
on the latest situation along the line of control, PTI reported
from Jammu.
</P>
<P>
The military attaches are from the United States, the United
Kingdom, Kenya, and Asian, East European and Middle East
countries. 
</P>
