<HEADLINE> Xi'an Hosts International Juvenile Wind Ensemble Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, August 7 (xinhua) -- An international juvenile wind
ensemble festival opened today in Xi'an, capital of northwest
China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The six-day festival with the theme "friendship, exchanges,
unification and peace", has attracted 13 wind ensembles consisting
of middle school students from China and Japan.
</P>
<P>
The ensembles will stage a series of concerts and open-air
performances in the city.
</P>
<P>
The festival is sponsored by the China and Shaanxi Musicians
Association. 
</P>
