<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman on South China Sea Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Ministry Spokesman Tang
Guoqiang today reiterated that Huangyan Island in South China Sea
has been an inherent part of Chinese territory since ancient times
and the Chinese government maintained a consistent position on
related issues.
</P>
<P>
Tang made the remarks today in response to a question
concerning the issue surrounding the fact that the U.S. and
Philippine air forces recently conducted military maneuvers near
the island.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese government has consistently advocated
peaceful settlements to disputes through consultations in order to
maintain peace and stability of the region.
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that concerned countries will adopt a prudent
attitude and exert greater efforts to promote regional peace and
stability.  
</P>
</TEXT>
