<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IMF Okays Third Annual ESAF Loan for Mali </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The International Monetary
Fund (IMF) announced Friday the approval of the third annual loan
for Mali under the Enhanced Structural Adjustment Facility (ESAF),
equivalent to about 28 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The resources will be utilized to back the government's
economic program for 1998-1999. The loan is available in two equal
semiannual installments, the first of which is available
immediately.
</P>
<P>
The government's medium-term development strategy aims to
consolidate macroeconomic stability and reach sustainable economic
growth that will help reduce poverty and raise the people's living
standards. The main macroeconomic objectives for 1998-99 program
include a real GDP growth of 5 percent, consumer price inflation
of 2 to 3 percent, and an external current account deficit of 8
percent.
</P>
<P>
Mali joined the IMF in September 1963. Its quota is about 92
million dollars and its outstanding use of IMF resources totaled
about 167 million dollars by the end of July, this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
