<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Forty-One Die in Chongqing Rainstorms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Forty-one people have died, 41
are missing and 156 have sustained injuries resulting from
rainstorms which ravaged the southwestern section of Chongqing, an
industrial center in southwest China, from early yesterday evening
to late this morning.
</P>
<P>
The storms, with dropped precipitation ranging from 150 to 300
millimeters, hit Qijiang, Jiangjin and Wansheng and caused
mudflows and rock slides which disrupted traffic on the
Chongqing-Guiyang Railway and the Chongqing-Guiyang and
Chongqing-Changsha highways.
</P>
<P>
A total of 5.1 million local people were adversely affected by
the storm which killed 20,000 head of livestock and damaged crops
on 215,000 hectares.  
</P>
</TEXT>
