<HEADLINE> Seven Boats Sunken to Hold Back Most Floodwaters in Jiujiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Seven boats have by far been
dumped into a 40-meter breach of the city defence embankments in
Jiujiang City, east China's Jiangxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Bags of rice, soybean, and stones were also used for the
effort. As a result, most of the raging floodwaters have been
blocked, however, there are still some sneaking out into the city
through gaps between the sunken boats.
</P>
<P>
Now, thousands of soldiers and civilians are working to plug up
the breach, using more boats and other materials. And another
1,700 armed police are rushing to reinforce the effort, sources
said. 
</P>
