<HEADLINE> Audi Pre-tax Profits Up in First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 7 (Xinhua) -- German carmaker Audi said Friday its
pre-tax profits surged nearly two thirds to 804 million marks (446
million U.S. dollars) in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Audi's turnover increased by 26.6 percent to 13.4 billion marks
(7.4 billion dollars) during the period, from sales of 303,000
cars, up 10 percent over the first half of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The company, a subsidiary of Europe's largest carmaker
Volkswagen (VW), reported drops in sales at home and Japan in the
first six months. But in the United States sales surged 19.9
percent to 20,410 cars, it said.
</P>
<P>
According to Audi, its A6 and A8 models were very successful on
the market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
