On August 2-3, a Tutsi-led rebellion erupted in Kinshasa, the
capital city of DRC and it soon spread to the eastern part of the
country, where it borders Uganda and Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
At a recent press conference, DRC President Laurent Kabila was
reported to have accused Rwanda and Uganda of formenting the
rebellion in his country and threatened to wage a war against
Rwanda if the situation continues to worsen. 
