<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dutch Justice Minister Pledges Fight Against Child Porn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The new Dutch minister of
justice pledged on Friday to intensify the fight against child
pornography in the country.
</P>
<P>
Benk Korthals made tackling child pornography a policy priority
and urged the set-up of a European Union-wide network of national
child porn database that will facilitate information exchange
between national investigative agencies.
</P>
<P>
In a letter addressed to the Dutch parliament, the justice
minister, who was sworn in this Monday alongside Prime Minister
Wim Kok, said that faster procedures are needed for international
judicial investigation on the Internet in addition to existing
legal assistance treaties.
</P>
<P>
This is expected, he added, to lead to more effective action
against child pornography on the computer network.
</P>
<P>
The justice minister said that the number of convictions in
child pornography cases in the Netherlands has risen from three in
1994, prior to the introduction of heavier sentences, to 27 in the
last 18 months.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch authorities have time and again expressed their
determination to clamp down on child pornography and the Dutch
police are conducting investigation in close cooperation with its
peer in neighboring Belgium and Germany.
</P>
<P>
Germany, Sweden and the Netherlands have already started
setting up the necessary database as an intensified step in the
fight. 
</P>
</TEXT>
