<HEADLINE> Global Youth Conference on Hunger Opens in Addis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Hassen Abdela, Ethiopian
Minister of Social and Labor Friday urged that priority be given
to children and youths so as to develop their physical, mental,
spiritual resources.
</P>
<P>
In his opening speech at the 3rd Global Youth Conference for
the End of Hunger here, Hassen said necessary conditions should
be fulfilled for their healthy development and growth.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the situation in Africa, the Ethiopian minister
said, there is high rate of infant mortality, malnutrition, lack
of adequate clean water and sanitation on the continent.
</P>
<P>
"Many African countries are confronted with economic
difficulties due to high external debt which hinders them from
allocating sufficient resources to provide for the general
education and welfare of children," he said.
</P>
<P>
The conference is the first one which is held in Africa. More
than 100 youth from 12 countries are attending the three-day
meeting.
</P>
<P>
According to figures available, 13 to 18 million people die
each year as a result of hunger and starvation. A total of
35,000 lives are lost every 24 hours. And 24 die every minute, 18
of whom are children under the age of five.
</P>
<P>
During the three-day meeting, participants will examine and
make proposals based on reports on progress made so far in
efforts to advance the cause of the global initiative. 
</P>
