seven years.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Lebanese journalists, Al-Sumait said
Kuwait is trying to turn to any media which enjoy international
influence and can help win the release of the Kuwaiti prisoners.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the Lebanese media, the freest in Arab countries,
can play a positive role.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwaiti official arrived here Wednesday for a four-day
visit after trips to Egypt and Syria. He said his ongoing tour is
part of Kuwait's international campaign for the freedom of those
still being jailed.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait has accused Iraq of holding more than 600 Kuwaitis since
the 1991 Gulf War which ended Iraq's seven-month-long occupation
of the sheikdom. Iraq, however, rejected the accusation.
</P>
<P>
Al-Sumait expressed Kuwait's support for Lebanon's resistance
against Israeli occupation of its southern territories, saying his
country will continue extending both material and moral support to
Lebanon's cause to recover occupied lands.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a 1,200-square-kilometer security zone in south
Lebanon in 1985 after two invasions, to allegedly protect its
northern areas from cross-border attacks by Lebanese guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
Al-Sumait said that an exhibition on the sufferings and pains
of the Lebanese people inflicted by the Israeli occupation will be
open in Kuwait to evoke Kuwaiti people's sympathy and support for
the Lebanese people.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, the Kuwaiti minister has held talks with
Lebanese leaders and officials on regional affairs and bilateral
ties. 
