<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eastern Chinese Province Fighting Smugglers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The fight against smuggling has
had some success in China's Zhejiang Province, where 450 million
yuan worth of smuggled goods were seized from January 1997 to the
middle part of this year.
</P>
<P>
Chai Songyue, the governor of this coastal province, made a
point of saying that Zhejiang will never permit smuggling as a
means of helping its local economy and that those who dare to
smuggle goods into the province are going to be penalized.
</P>
<P>
From January 1997 to the middle part of this year, the
province stopped 3,362 acts of smuggling, confiscating 86,000
cartons of cigarettes, 39,000 tons of oil products, 5,041 tons of
chemical materials, and a large amount of other goods.
</P>
<P>
Chai says that, in order to deal with a changing situation, the
province has begun a new crusade against smuggling, focusing on
oil products, automobiles, motorcycles, cigarettes,
telecommunications equipment, and chemicals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
