<HEADLINE> Fromberg Beats Kucera to Reach Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Australian Richard Fromberg
stunned top-seeded Karol Kucera of Slovakia 6-1, 6-7 (4-7), 6-4
to reach his second finals of the year in the ATP Tour event in
Amsterdam, the Netherlands, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old sixth seed, who lost his previous final to
former number one Marcelo Rios of Chile in Auckland in January,
will vie for the title against Magnus Norman of Sweden, who won
the final berth after beating Mariano Zabaleta of Argentina 7-5,
6-4. 
</P>
