<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO -- Foreign Minister of the Republic of Congo Rodolphe
Adada left here for home Saturday after wrapping up a three-day
visit to Egypt, the Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa, who saw him off at the
airport, told reporters that Adada conveyed a message to President
Hosni Mubarak from Congolese President Denis Sassou-Nguess. But he
did not disclose its content. (Egypt-Congo-FM)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NAIROBI -- One hundred and eight people were killed and 4,149
others injured in Friday's car bombing near the U.S. embassy in
Nairobi's downtown area, Kenyan Foreign Minister Bonaya Godana
said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting with foreign envoys here, the minister said that
most of the injured have been given out-patient treatment while
over 500 wounded have been admitted at major hospitals in the
capital and 24 serious cases in the intensive care units.
(Kenya-Bombing Casualties)
</P>
