TEHRAN -- A road accident killed 15 people and injured an
unspecified number of others early Saturday in southwestern Iran,
the official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Traffic police said that a bus collided with a truck about 50
kilometers from southwestern port city of Bushehr, due to
narrowness of the road, and high speed and deviation to the left
of the bus. (Iran-Accident-Toll)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkey has called on the international community for
urgent interference to stop the bloodshed in the Yugoslav province
of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued Friday by the Foreign Ministry said that
"We are deeply concerned with the continuing violence and clashes
in Kosovo, which have led to mass waves of refugees. The fact that
the operations of the Yugoslav security forces (in Kosovo) that
have led to such grave consequences as mass graves provokes a deep
anger in the Turkish public." (Turkey-Kosovo)
</P>
