DAR ES SALAAM -- Tanzanian Vice-President Omar Ali Juma said
Saturday morning that his country will cooperate with the United
States in tracking those who are responsible for the bombing of
the U.S. embassy in Dar es Salaam.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president made the remarks during a tour to the
embassy which was wrecked by a horrifying bomb at about 10:45
a.m. Friday which left at least seven people dead and more than 70
others injured. (Tanzania-Bomb-Condemnation)
</P>
<P>
