<HEADLINE> Yeltsin: Russia to Cooperate in Countering Terrorism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 8 (Xinhua) --- Russia is ready to increase
cooperation with the United States and other countries in
eradicating terrorism, Russian President Boris Yeltsin stated on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Soon after he learned about the explosions outside U.S.
embassies in Kenya and Tanzania, Yeltsin sent a message to
President Bill Clinton expressing indignation over the incident,
the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
