Meanwhile, Russian Foreign Ministry spokesman Valery
Nesterushkin also said that Moscow strongly denounced such
barbaric actions.
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that the local authorities "will take all
the necessary measures to establish the identity and punish those
who organized and committed those crimes".
</P>
<P>
The explosions, which occurred on Friday morning, left at
least 107 people dead and triggered a wave of indignation all over
the world. 
