<HEADLINE> Henry Wants to Join Arsenal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 8 (Xinhua) -- France's World Cup winger Thierry
Henry said on Saturday that he wants to leave Monaco for English
premier league side Arsenal.
</P>
<P>
But Monaco president Jean-Louis Campora did not want to talk
about the issue about Henry's future.
</P>
<P>
"I want to leave and it's to Arsenal and not anywhere else that
I want to go," Henry said.
</P>
<P>
He said Arsenal directors had been in contact with Campora over
the telephone. But "the president won't answer my request. I'm
disappointed," Henry, 21 in nine days time, said.
</P>
<P>
Henry has three years still to run on his contract with
Monaco. 
</P>
