<HEADLINE> Rehhagel Not Keen on Coaching German National Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Otto Rehhagel, who coached
Kaiserslautern to German champions, said on Saturday he was not
interested in coaching the falling German national team.
</P>
<P>
"I'm not keen on that job," Rehhagel said. "Even if it was
offered to me, I would not take it."
</P>
<P>
Rehhagel, who made Kaiserslautern the first promoted side to
win the Bundesliga title, said he intended to stay with them until
2000.
</P>
<P>
"Then, I will perhaps go abroad," Rehhagel, who will turn 60
on Sunday, said. "England would be interesting. I really like
their kind of football." 
</P>
</TEXT>
