<HEADLINE> Chinese Historical Relics Exhibit In Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 8 (Xinhua) -- A seven-month exhibit of Chinese
historical relics unearthed in Sichuan Province in southwest China
have been getting a good reception recently in Japan.
</P>
<P>
The exhibit started in April and will run to October. On
display are 225 gold ornaments, bronze carvings, pieces of
pottery, and jade weapons and tools that are 4000 years old.
</P>
<P>
They were discovered at the Sanxingdui Site in the city of
Guanghan, 40 km from the provincial capital Chengdu, since 1929.
</P>
<P>
The exhibit has so far attracted 150,000 Japanese visitors.
</P>
</TEXT>
