<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Hang Seng Bank has contributed
a sum of 500,000 HK dollars (about 64,100 U.S. dollars) to the
Hong Kong Red Cross China Relief Fund for relief operations for
the Yangtze River flood victims.
</P>
