<HEADLINE> HKSAR Customs Delegation Visit Mainland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 8 (Xinhua) -- A five-member delegation of the
Hong Kong Customs returned here Saturday after a five-day visit to
China's mainland.
</P>
<P>
Lawrence Li Shu-fai, commissioner of Customs and Excise of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) of China, said that
the visit could further assist well in curbing smuggling
activities.
</P>
<P>
Li led the delegation to Beijing on August 3. "We have met our
counterparts of the Customs General Administration of the People's
Republic of China and discussed formally our co-operation and
liaison arrangements," said Li.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, both sides had agreed to further strengthen
their co-operation and enhance the exchange of intelligence.
</P>
<P>
"After the meeting, we have signed a formal Memorandum of
Understanding on Co-operation to substantiate the agreements
reached during an informal meeting held in Hong Kong earlier this
year," Li said.
</P>
<P>
Both sides have also discussed the latest developments in
respective Customs administrations and explored ways to curb
smuggling activities, he added.
</P>
<P>
In Beijing, the Hong Kong delegation have also met the
Commissioner of the Customs General Administration of PRC, Qian
Guan-lin.
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of the Customs General Administration, the
party visited the Administration's foreign affairs training
institute in Suzhou before meeting the Chief of the Nanjing
Customs House, Chen Zheng-gong, and the Chief of the Suzhou
Customs House, Wang Jin-xing.
</P>
<P>
After it returned to China on July 1, 1997, Hong Kong remained
a separate Customs territory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
