<HEADLINE> Road Accident Kills 15 in Southern Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 8 (Xinhua) -- A road accident killed 15 people
and injured an unspecified number of others early Saturday in
southwestern Iran, the official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Traffic police said that a bus collided with a truck about 50
kilometers from southwestern port city of Bushehr, due to
narrowness of the road, and high speed and deviation to the left
of the bus.
</P>
<P>
The were 38 passengers on the bus when the accident happened,
the report said. It is now known how many people were injuried.
