<HEADLINE> 12 Killed in Road Accident in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Twelve people were killed
in an accident in Durban Saturday when a minibus taxi collided
with a car and both burst into flames, a provincial transport
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
South African Press Association (SAPA) quoted Ranjeni
Munusamy, KwaZulu-Natal provincial transport spokesman, as saying
that the tragedy occurred around noon.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the car, a Porsche, allegedly tried to make a
U-turn on the barrier line, Munusamy said.
</P>
<P>
"An oncoming taxi slammed into the car and both vehicle burst
into flames," said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The Porsche's driver and passenger as well as 10 people in the
taxi were burnt to death.
</P>
<P>
Five other passengers in the taxi were injured and taken to
hospital in Durban. Their conditions are not known yet. 
</P>
