<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey Urges Interference Into Kosovo Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Turkey has called on the
international community for urgent interference to stop the
bloodshed in the Yugoslav province of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued Friday by the Foreign Ministry said that
"We are deeply concerned with the continuing violence and clashes
in Kosovo, which have led to mass waves of refugees. The fact that
the operations of the Yugoslav security forces (in Kosovo) that
have led to such grave consequences as mass graves provokes a deep
anger in the Turkish public."
</P>
<P>
The statement emphasized that insensitivity to the situation
in Kosovo is unacceptable. It called on the international
community and organizations to immediately accelerate efforts
aimed at ending the violence in Kosovo and find a peaceful
solution.
</P>
<P>
"A non-conditional and substantial dialog, based on the
principles of the United Nations and the Organization for
Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE) should be initiated as
soon as possible," the statement added.
</P>
<P>
It pointed out that the settlement process should include
representatives of all peoples in Kosovo, including the Turkish
minority, and should be aimed at establishing a democratic and
pluralist administration which would guarantee the legitimate
rights of all people in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has deep-rooted historical, humanitarian and cultural
ties with Kosovo and a considerable number of Turks are still
living in the region.
</P>
<P>
Since February, fierce fighting has erupted between the
Serbian forces and ethnic Albanian guerrillas who demand
independence from Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The bloodshed has claimed many innocent lives and led to a
large number of refugees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
