<HEADLINE> Concrete Actions Are Needed Against Smuggling: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Wu Yi, an alternative member of
the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee's Political Bureau,
said here today that effective measures and concrete actions are
the key to success of the country's campaign against smuggling.
</P>
<P>
Wu made the remarks at the end of a four-day tour of the
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, where she talked with customs
officers and local people, and was shown automobiles that had been
confiscated while being smuggled and motorboats that had been
smuggled into the autonomous region.
</P>
<P>
Wu asked Party committees and local government to increase the
campaign against smuggling and to improve the local people's
awareness of the law. She said that customs officers should be
provided with the most advanced equipment to improve their combat
effectiveness.  
</P>
