<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Opens Food Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The 1998 Hong Kong Food
Festival was opened here Saturday to offer a golden opportunity
for food lovers to taste a wide range of western and eastern
cuisine.
</P>
<P>
At the 16-day event, a series of colorful activities will be
staged, such as cooking with master chefs, gourmet dining around
Hong Kong, waiters' competition and food bazaar, according to the
organizer, the Hong Kong Tourist Association (HKTA).
</P>
<P>
With one restaurant for every 720 residents, Hong Kong is known
as the culinary capital of Asia, where gourmets can find cuisine
ranging from Cantonese to Shanghainese, from Mexican to
Mediterranean, and from Korean to Indonesian.
</P>
<P>
Since it was launched in 1986, the food festival has been
closely tied to the promotion of Hong Kong tourism, Y S Lo,
chairman of the HKTA, said at the opening ceremony Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Newly added to this year's festival are special culinary tours,
which help people gain an understanding of the traditional aspects
of Chinese life related to food. Participants in the Healthy
Living Tour, for instance, can watch performance of Qigong
exercise, visit a herbalist's store and eat a healthy meal.
</P>
<P>
District food festivals were also kicked off Saturday in Lei
Yue Mun, Kowloon City and Lan Kwai Fong. Lei Yue Mun is where
people can eat the best seafood; Kowloon City, a district
surrounding the already closed Kai Tak Airport, is known for its
numerous restaurants serving a variety of Asian foods, such as
Thai, Cantonese and Chiu Chau; and Lan Kwai Fong gathers trendy
bars and restaurants with international flavor.
</P>
<P>
Two celebrity culinary guides were published Saturday to the
gastronomic and sightseeing sites in Kowloon City and Causeway
Bay, the central business district in Hong Kong Island. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
