<HEADLINE> China on DPP Attempt to Undermine Cross-Strait Relations (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As to the reason that some DPP members made use of such a
criminal case resultant from from a business dispute between the
people across the Taiwan Straits, the article attributes it to
their obstinate adherence to the stance of "Taiwan independence."
</P>
<P>
They always want to seize a chance to land the mainland into a
position of "an antagonistic country," act as "heroes" to obtain
more votes, and pass themselves off as "the oppressed" to win the
sympathy of the international community, the article says.
</P>
<P>
