<HEADLINE> Aids Spreading Fast in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 8 (Xinhua) -- HIV/AIDS carriers in Vietnam are
estimated to be between 90,000-100,000 and likely to rise to
200,000 by 2000, Vietnam News Agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The report said 59 out of the total 61 provinces and cities
have found HIV/AIDS carriers, with two provinces in the northern
mountain region being reportedly free from this fatal disease.
</P>
<P>
It said ten localities having the highest number of HIV
positive include six southern and four northern
provinces.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that of the total HIV/AIDS carriers, 65 percent
were drug addicts, 5 percent, prostitutes. 
</P>
