<HEADLINE> New Expressway Operational in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 8 (Xinhua) -- An expressway linking Tieling
and Siping cities in Liaoning Province of northeast China, opened
to traffic today, marking the completion of an expressway between
Shenyang, the provincial capital, and Siping.
</P>
<P>
The Shenyang-Siping Expressway, which is 160 km in length and
costs 2.6 billion yuan, is a major part of a trunk expressway from
Beijing, capital of China, to Harbin, capital of the northernmost
Chinese province of Heilongjiang.
</P>
<P>
To date, Liaoning, a major heavy industrial base in China, has
built 707 km of expressways, leading all the provinces,
municipalities and ethnic autonomous regions in China. 
</P>
