<HEADLINE> Taliban Militia captures Mazar-i- Sharif </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan Taliban militia
Saturday captured the strategic northern town of Mazar-i-Sharif
after three hours of heavy fighting, a senior Taliban official
based in Islamabad told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Abdul Hakeem Mujahid, the chief representative of the Taliban
militia in Islamabad, said he had received reports from
Mazar-i-Sharif, the headquarters of the anti-Taliban Northern
Alliance that the Taliban has taken full control of the city.
</P>
<P>
According to other Taliban sources, a total of 5,000 Taliban
troops took part in Saturday's fighting which started 10 a.m.
(local time) from Daulatabad area in the northern city.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban forces used jet planes, conducting air raids
against the military targets of the Northern Alliance.
</P>
<P>
Relief agencies have already withdrawn from the city in fear of
the fighting after the Taliban captured Shiberghan, capital of
Jawzjan province last Sunday. 
</P>
