<HEADLINE> Nigerian Drug Manufacturers Want Free Duty on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's drug manufacturers have
urged the government to scrap duties on imported raw materials to
save them from imminent collapse, local media said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Yomi Osewa, the national chairman of the Nigerian Association
of Industrial Pharmacists (NAIP) made the call Friday in Lagos
while briefing media on the NAIP's first national conference.
</P>
<P>
The chairman also asked the government to ban the import of
drugs that can be produced locally to discourage the so-called
dumping of sub-standard and inferior products in the country.
</P>
<P>
The coming conference, he said, will try to find ways to
revive the country's drug producing sector in a depressed
economy.
</P>
<P>
Osewa urged the government to properly fund and staff various
agencies charged with the responsibility of controlling and
monitoring drug importations. 
