<DOCNO> XIE19980808.0141 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ranariddh Reaffirms Rejection of Elections Results </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Deposed first prime minister
Prince Norodom Ranariddh reaffirmed here on Saturday that he and
his party Funcinpec would not accept the results of the elections.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at Funcinpec's headquarters, Ranariddh said, "we ask
to revote in some constituencies which have serious election
fraud, and to revive the former formula of seat allocation."
</P>
<P>
Regarding Funcinpec's coalition with the Cambodian People's
Party (CPP), he said it would be decided by Funcinpec's leadership.
</P>
<P>
But Funcinpec would first count the final result after the
investigation and verification on election's fraud. Otherwise
Funcinpec's parliamentarians would not take part in the meeting
of the National Assembly, he added.
</P>
<P>
Funcinpec would ask for the post of National Assembly chairman,
which is now held by CPP President Chea Sim, Ranariddh
continued.
</P>
<P>
Ranariddh stressed that the next government must be a
three-party coalition to be made up of CPP, Funcinpec
and SRP.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Ranariddh vowed he would not participate in the
government led by Hun Sen, because the Cambodian people would
oppose him to do so, and he himself also has lost confidence in
Hun Sen.
</P>
<P>
He believed that Hun Sen could not take any measure to resolve
the problems faced by Cambodia now, such as national security,
corruption and Vietnamese immigrants.
</P>
<P>
Funcinpec and the Sam Rainsy Party (SRP), claiming election
fraud, now unite to oppose the common rival -- the CPP, and have
vowed not to form any coalition government with the it unless
there is a new election in the disputed areas.
</P>
<P>
But most analysts here expect Funcinpec to contest the results
first and then agree to a coalition in return for concessions.
</P>
</TEXT>
