the other Friday morning near the U.S. embassies in Nairobi and
Dares Salaam, killing about 80 people and injured more than 1,000
others.
</P>
<P>
A 150-member Israeli rescue and medical team as well as
medicine supplies are ready to be flied to Nairobi later Saturday
morning to help the victims, Israel Radio said.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordechai called his
U.S. counterpart William Cohen Friday night to express his
condolence for the casualties and tell him of Israel's readiness
to provide every assistance which was needed, according to the
radio. 
