<HEADLINE> Yangtze Water Level Fluctuating As Smaller Dykes Collapse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Water level of the Yangtze River
has been fluctuating and is still below the danger line of 45
meters at the Shashi Measuring Point, set for a flood diversion in
Gong'an County, in central China's Hubei Province, owing to
unexpected breaches of two smaller dykes downstream this morning.
</P>
<P>
Latest reports show that the water level at the Zhicheng
Measuring Point plummeted by a dozen cm as two smaller auxiliary
dykes breached 50 km east of Gong'an County where the Jingjiang
Flood Diversion Zone is located.
</P>
<P>
Last night, a local expert forecast that the water level will
possibly top the 45 m-level, saying if the level reaches that high
and even poises to climb further, the diversion scheme has to be
carried out by blasting part of Yangtze embankments and releasing
floodwater through the North Flood Gate.
</P>
<P>
Local people still prepare themselves for the proposed
diversion scheme by efforts to evacuate the diversion zones from
Thursady and conduct exercises for diversion and check-up
equipment at the North Flood Gate nearby the Yangtze Embankments.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
