<HEADLINE> Dhaka Beefs up Security in, Around Diplomatic Enclave </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Security has been beefed up in and
around the diplomatic enclave in the capital of Bangladesh
following the explosions at the U.S. embassies in Kenya and
Tanzania Friday.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Embassy in Bangladesh requested the government to
tighten up the existing security measures at the mission, press
reports Saturday quoted officials as saying.
</P>
<P>
Security guards have been put on alert in the Baridhara area,
where most of the foreign embassies in the country are located,
and the government has also taken steps to ensure fool-proof
security for the U.S. officials in Dhaka following the request.
</P>
<P>
The safety measures for the diplomatic enclave were tightened,
specially for the United States mission in view of the situation
abroad, a police high official said.
</P>
<P>
Over 100 people were killed and more 1,000 injured in separate
detonations of powerful bombs occurred at the U.S. embassies in
Kenya and Tanzania Friday, Press reports said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
