<HEADLINE> Russia: Kosovo Crisis Can Not Be Solved by Arms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Russian deputy foreign
minister Nikolaj Afanasjevski said on Friday that the Kosovo
crisis could not be solved through military means, the Tanjug news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
After meeting with Ibrahim Rugava, political leader of Kosovo's
ethnic Albanian majority in Pristina, Afanasjevski also ruled out
the possibility of foreign military intervention in the crisis.
</P>
<P>
He said the only way to settle the crisis is resumption of
talks between the Serbian authorities and the ethnic Albanians to
find a political solution, the Yugoslav news agency said.
</P>
<P>
Afanasjevski pointed out that both sides -- the Serbian
authorities and the ethnic Albanians -- should ensure that all
refugees fleeing the conflict return to their homes as early as
possible. 
</P>
