<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Irrigated Cropland Increases in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yangon, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The irrigated cropland amounted to
1.94 million hectares in the 1997-98 fiscal year which ended in
March, 87,010 hectares more than the previous year, according to
official statistics.
</P>
<P>
The increase was due to the expanded irrigated area for summer
paddy cultivation, said a latest annual report on agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture, which is the mainstay of Myanmar's economy
traditionally accounting for 35 to 40 percent of the gross
domestic product (GDP) and 35 percent of the export, grew by 2.9
percent in its output value in the 1997-98 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
In the year, a total of eight irrigation facilities were built
in the country, irrigating 184,072 hectares of farmland.
</P>
<P>
The completed irrigation facilities in the whole country added
up to 90 since late 1988, of which 22 are in central Mandalay
division where arid zones lie.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to increased irrigation facilities, the production of
paddy, one of the four pillar crops of Myanmar, went up to 17.3
million tons in 1997-98. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
