<HEADLINE> Yangtze River Water Level Begins to Fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The water level of the Yangtze
River at the city of Shashi has begun to fall as the latest flood
crest smoothly passed the city early this morning.
</P>
<P>
The fourth crest passed Shashi between 4:00 am and 6:00 am
today, bringing the water level down from 44.95 m to 44.93 m at
11:00 am and 44.92 m at 12:00, according to sources at the Shashi
Measuring Point, upstream of Wuhan.
</P>
<P>
However, the flooding situation remained severe as water rushes
down from the upper reaches and water at the lower reaches recedes
at a very slow pace, the source said.
</P>
<P>
At 24:00 pm Friday, water level at Shashi buoyed up to 44.92 m,
compared with 44.88 m at just two hours before.  
</P>
</TEXT>
