<HEADLINE> Two Chinese Firms to Issue Corporate Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Two major Chinese firms will
start to issue a total of 38.5 million US dollars worth corporate
bonds beginning today and Monday, according to China Daily today.
</P>
<P>
Real estate firm Beijing Huayuan Property Co. will offer 120
million yuan (about 14.5 million US dollars) worth of three-year
bonds from now through September 6. The firm will then apply for
listing on one of China's stock exchanges in Shanghai or Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
Huayuan is a joint-venture in property development jointly
started in late 1994 with Jianshi Development Co, a wholly-owned
subsidiary of China Resources Beijing Ltd, a Hong Kong-listed
red-chip firm.
</P>
<P>
Money from the bond issue will be used in a five-billion yuan
(602.4 million US Dollars) property renovation project in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Dongfeng Motor Corp., a joint venture with French
auto maker PSA Peugeot Citron in central Hubei Province, will
issue 200 million yuan (about 24 million US dollars) worth of
three-year bonds starting Monday through September 10.
</P>
<P>
The funds raised through the bond issue will be used to finance
Dongfeng's new project to manufacture car parts. The project is
expected to generate annual sales of 1.97 billion yuan (237.3
million US dollars).  
</P>
