<HEADLINE> HK Firms Interested in Investing in Shandong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Trade Development
Council (TDC) said that at least two of the six companies that
toured State-owned enterprises in Shandong last month have started
active negotiations to form joint venture.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong-based Atlas Magnetics Manufacturing Ltd is currently
negotiating with Qingdao Micro-motor Factory and Qingdao Connector
Factory to thrash out deals on setting up a joint venture for the
production of ferrite products and magnetic connectors, today's
China Daily reported, quoting Ricky Cheung, president of Atlas
Magnetics Manufacturing Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Cheung said that if Atlas cooperates with the Shandong SOEs, it
can cut 10 percent from depreciation costs of certain product
lines.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong-based Trigo Enterprises Ltd, which is considering
setting up joint ventures with SOEs on the bus production in
Shandong, has approached the Chinese National Heavy Vehicle Corp
and the Qingdao City Special Vehicle Manufacturing Corp and the
Qingdao-Pacific Passenger Vehicle Co. Ltd, Johnny Wan, manager of
the TDC said.
</P>
<P>
If deals are struck, agreements to be signed will be worth at
least 249 million yuan (about 30 million US dollars), he said.
</P>
<P>
Recently, investment policies in China have been relaxed,
making it easier for companies to take part in joint ventures,
said Dominic Yin, managing director of Trigo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
