<HEADLINE> Cross Cultural Issues in Aviation to Be Discussed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The Asia and Pacific office of
the International Civil Aviation Organization (ICAO) will host a
seminar and workshop on cross cultural issues in aviation in
Bangkok from August 12 to 14, the newspaper The Bangkok Post
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be attended by more than 80 representatives
from government civil aviation authorities, airlines and other
private and government aviation entities from 17 countries in the
Asia and Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The seminar is the latest event in a series of regional
seminars and worldwide symposia which have been organized by ICAO
since 1991 as part of its flight safety and human factors program.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will focus upon cultural issues because culture
influences how humans interact with one another and with
technology within the aviation environment. 
