<HEADLINE> Special Police Bureau Set Up in Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 8 (Xinhua) -- A Special Police Bureau (SPB) has
been set up here recently to deal with abuse of children,
adolescents and women, according to police here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The SPB will receive complaints and take action in cases of
abuse of children, adolescents and women, sexual harassment and
other forms of ill-treatment, police sources said.
</P>
<P>
The activities of the bureau will extend to the country's all
divisions and will include investigations, supervision of
investigations or giving direction where necessary to police in
instances where such cases have been reported in any part of the
country.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the SPB will be headed by a senior
superintendent, to be assisted by several senior and junior police
officers.
</P>
<P>
Police authority has directed the SPB to take all steps to
educate the public and create an awareness of the existence of
this bureau to deal with harassment and abuse of women, child
slavery, cruelty to children and other related matters, they
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
