<HEADLINE> Czech Police Break Drug Trafficking Ring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Czech police broke up a
transnational drug trafficking ring and arrested 17 suspects in a
recent anti-drug operation.
</P>
<P>
A police spokesman told reporters Friday that a large amount of
narcotics, including cocaine and heroine, were seized during
the operation carried out on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He said the seized drug had a street value of billions of Czech
korun (31 korun worth about one U.S. dollar), the largest in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
The operation, dubbed "Award," was carried out with the help of
the Netherlands and Ukrainian police.
</P>
<P>
The arrested suspects includes two Czechs and 15 Netherlanders.
</P>
<P>
Drug traffickers have made the Czech Republic, located in the
heart of Europe, a trading center by taking advantage of its easy
access to other countries. 
</P>
