<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Five U.S. Children Trapped in Car Trunk Die of Heat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Five children died of heat
exposure in Utah on Friday when they were trapped while playing in
the trunk of a car.
</P>
<P>
The girls, two sisters, two cousins and the fifth was being
cared for by the mother of one of the children, were between the
age of two and six, the Associated Press said.
</P>
<P>
Local police said they were in the trunk for about one hour and
the cause of death is heat exposure as the temperatures reached
the upper 30s centigrade in the Salt Lake City area Friday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Police were called to the scene when one parent become alarmed
that the children were missing. A search of the car turned up the
bodies.
</P>
<P>
Police said there were no witnesses who saw the girls climb
into the trunk. It was not immediately known how they got in the
car, how they selected that car or how they became trapped.
</P>
<P>
The Utah tragedy comes after two recent cases in which young
children died after getting into the trunks of cars.
</P>
<P>
Two boys were found dead Sunday in Greensboro, Pennsylvania,
after they apparently crawled into the trunk of their parents car.
</P>
<P>
On July 13, four young cousins in Gallup, New Mexico, died of
heat and asphyxiation after climbing in the trunk of a car.
</P>
</TEXT>
