<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Electricity Use Slips in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Electricity consumption in
Thailand in the first half of this year dropped by 2.3 percent
year-on-year to 46,688 megawatts as a result of the recession,
according to figures released by the National Energy Policy Office
available Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Peak power demand declined by 0.6 percent in the period to
14,180 megawatts.
</P>
<P>
Bangkok recorded the sharpest drop of 3.8 percent while usage
in the provinces rose by 2.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Among consumer sectors, industries registered the highest
decline of 15 percent, government offices 10 percent and the
commercial sector 4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Consumption rose by 15 percent in the residential sector and by
2 percent among small businesses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
