<HEADLINE> Six Injured in Explosions at U.S. Propane Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 7 (Xinhua) -- At least six people were
seriously injured in a series of explosions at a propane company
in Cincinnati on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Four workers ran out of the Auxier Gas Co., about 35 kilometers
east of Cincinnati, with their clothes burned, a firefighter was
quoted by the Associated Press as saying.
</P>
<P>
Six males, aging 17 to 52, were taken to University Hospital in
Cincinnati. Their conditions ranged from fair to critical.
</P>
<P>
The explosion peeled away the aluminum walls of the company's
main building where thousands of gallons of propane were stored.
</P>
<P>
More than a dozen businesses were evacuated, and smoke could be
seen kilometers away.
</P>
<P>
The fire was controlled by firefighters within two hours of the
explosions. But it was not yet known what caused blasts.
</P>
<P>
The company, which distributes propane to homes and businesses,
stores an average of 10,000 gallons of propane. 
</P>
