<HEADLINE> China Building New Port in Jiangsu Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 8 (Xinhua) -- China is building a large sea
port in Dafeng, a city in the central part of east China's Jiangsu
Province.
</P>
<P>
The Dafeng Port, with a designed annual handling capacity of
4.3 million tons and a budgeted cost of 480 million yuan (57.8
million US dollars), can be accessed by ocean-going vessels of
100,000 dead-weight tons.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the port includes two 5,000-ton bulk cargo
wharves, one 3,000-ton wharf for liquid chemicals and a 4.3-km
dike. Construction of the first phase, which has an estimated
annual handling capacity of 800,000 tons, is scheduled for
completion in September of the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The second phase of the port is also being drafted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
