<HEADLINE> Sampras Battles to Quarter-finals At Du Maurier Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Top-ranked American Pete Sampras
battled to the quarter-finals at the du Maurier Open tennis event
in Toronto on Friday, beating Germany's Tommy Hass 7-5, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
In the first set, Sampras made a lot of errors against Hass,
the 41th in the world.
</P>
<P>
But Sampras, who appeared tied and sluggish, went on to take
control of the match with an early break in the second set.
</P>
<P>
"It's just a few points that cost me the first set," said the
20-year-old Hass.
</P>
<P>
"In the second he had the momentum going, and it's tough to
come back against an opponent like Pete," Hass said.
</P>
<P>
Sampras is to play eighth-seeded compatriot Andre Agassi in the
quarter-final match later Friday night.
</P>
<P>
Agassi, who has won this tournament three times, reached the
quarter-final round with a 2-6, 7-5, 6-3 victory over 10th-seeded
Croatian Goran Ivanisevic. 
</P>
