<HEADLINE> Death Toll of U.S. Tanzania Embassy Blast Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Seven people have been
killed while 58 others were injured, 18 of them seriously,
following a horrifying bomb explosion at the U. S. embassy in Dar
es Salaam on Friday morning, hospital sources said.
</P>
<P>
More than 20 cars and three motorcycles parked in the embassy
were wrecked while the explosion has damaged large part of the
office building and neighboring buildings, the police said.
</P>
<P>
