<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 7 (Xinhua) -- At least two people, both
are men, were killed in an explosion that happens in the U.S.
embassy in Dar es Salaam on Friday morning, Tanzanian Red Cross
Society officials said.
</P>
<P>
However, CNN said four people have been confirmed dead.
</P>
<P>
Casualties are not immediately known, said Ubwa Suleiman, the
information officer of the Tanzania Red Cross Society.
</P>
<P>
Police have sealed traffic to the embassy site.
</P>
<P>
