<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Produces More Tea to Meet Demand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian has enough tea
output at present to meet the local demand and to export its
surplus abroad, a report said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Tesegaye Berhane, General Manager of the
Coffee and Tea Authority of Ethiopia, as saying a total of 3,800
tons of tea was produced during the just ended 1997/98 fiscal
year (ending July 7) out of which 181 tons was supplied to the
foreign market.
</P>
<P>
The general manager recalled that the tea production could not
meet the local demand just a few years ago, saying that Ethiopian
tea is fast emerging competitive in European and other foreign
markets since they are of a high quality standard.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, out of the six-million hectares of land in
the country suitable for tea production, only 2,104 hectares have
so far been exploited. 
</P>
</TEXT>
