<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000 GMT, August 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA -- Naci Orhan, mayor of Bahcesaray city in southeastern
Turkey, was kidnaped by Kurdish militants, the Daily News
newspaper reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Rebels of the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party stopped Orhan's
car outside Bahcesaray Wednesday night and abducted him and three
others. (Turkey-Mayor-Abduction)
</P>
<P>
- - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Central Bank has decided to slash its key
lending rates by 1.5 percentage, local daily The Jerusalem Post
reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The report said following the change, which will take effect on
Sunday, the key lending rates will be 9.5 percent, the lowest
level since November 1993. (Israel-Interest Rate-Cut)
</P>
<P>
- - -
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- Cypriot President Glafcos Clerides said Friday that
Cyprus would not yield to foreign pressures over its planned
deployment of Russian-made S-300 anti-aircraft missiles.
</P>
<P>
He said that foreign officials have made suggestions on the
missile issue, and that the Cypriot government has replied
accordingly.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Greek Foreign Under-Secretary Yiannos Kranidiotis on
Friday briefed Cypriot Foreign Minister Ioannis Kasoulides on his
meeting in Athens early this week with United States Ambassador to
Greece Nicholas Burns on the missile issue. (Cyprus-Foreign
Pressures)
</P>
<P>
- - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Visiting Kuwaiti Information Minister Yusef Mohammad
Al-Sumait Friday called on Arab media to help seek the release of
Kuwaitis who have been jailed in Iraq for seven years.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Lebanese journalists, Al-Sumait said
Kuwait is trying to turn to any media which enjoy international
influence and can help win the release of the Kuwaiti prisoners.
</P>
<P>
Al-Sumait expressed Kuwait's support for Lebanon's resistance
against Israeli occupation of its southern territories, saying his
country will continue extending both material and moral support to
Lebanon's cause to recover occupied lands. (Lebanon-Kuwait-Media
Help) 
</P>
