<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Import, Export Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian import and export
increased during the 1997/98 fiscal year ended on July 7, as
compared with the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The National Bank of Ethiopia said Friday that a total of 1.2
billion U.S. Dollars had been disbursed for imported goods during
the period, an increase of 216 million U.S. Dollars or 22 percent
over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Similarly, a sum of over 618 million Dollars was obtained
during the same period from exported items, a rise of 14 million
Dollars.
</P>
<P>
The bank said that a total of 959.6 million Dollars was
supplied for public auction, out of which 851.5 million Dollars
was sold, representing an increase of 15.5 percent over sales
in the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
